	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><img src="http://files.slembcke.net/temp/NESStack.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/mLVJr026230">https://youtu.be/mLVJr026230</a><!-- m --><br /><br />So I've been working as a contractor on a game project for a local company. Everything about the game was ripe for a NES port, so as a weird joke, I decided to demake it for the NES. Tada! I think it turned out pretty good. I don't really want this to show up on Google (yet) since the game it's based on won't be released for a while. We want to have some fun with using the NES version as a marketing gimmick, and I don't want it to pollute search results for the actual game before it's even out. Gernfher Fgnpx in rot13 if you really want to know, just don't post it in plaintext please.<br /><br />On the off chance that anybody here is going to be in Minneapolis for 2D Con this weekend, it will be playable there. : D<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://files.slembcke.net/temp/StackingGame.nes.gz">http://files.slembcke.net/temp/StackingGame.nes.gz</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Controls:<br />Left/Right -&gt; Walk<br />A -&gt; Jump<br />B -&gt; Pickup / drop stack<br />Up + B -&gt; Grappling hook<br />Down + B -&gt; Pickup /drop block under player<br /><br />Anyway. Enjoy, and thanks for all the help. : D

		

